        introduction: "The Saint-Brieuc to Paris journey is a traverse across France, from the granite shores of the Pink Granite Coast and the bay of Saint-Brieuc — a national nature reserve — to the vibrant heart of the capital. Saint-Brieuc, Cotes-d'Armor prefecture, is an endearing city whose Breton character shows in every granite-paved lane, in its fortified cathedral towers and in its lively markets. The city occupies a spectacular natural site, perched on a plateau carved by the deep Gouedic and Gouet valleys. The Legue port, nestled in the Gouet estuary, is the maritime heart of the city. A few kilometres north, the Pink Granite Coast between Perros-Guirec and Tregastel displays a geological spectacle unique in the world: 300-million-year-old pink granite boulders sculpted by marine and wind erosion into fantastic shapes. This long 450 km journey to Paris is used by Breton families heading to the capital, business professionals and Parisian tourists joining northern Brittany for long weekends. The taxi offers superior comfort compared to the TGV, especially for large families, travellers with bulky luggage or sports equipment, and groups wanting a direct door-to-door service.",
