        conseils: "For this 4h30 journey, bring water, snacks and entertainment if travelling with children — the vehicle has USB charging ports. Your driver offers a comfort break at the halfway point, usually at Laval or Le Mans services. A81 and A11 tolls (about 40 euros) are included in the displayed price. For an evening arrival in Paris, provide your exact address so the driver can optimise the route into the capital. If your destination is CDG or Orly airport rather than central Paris, specify when booking — a supplement may apply. Before leaving Saint-Brieuc, a detour via the Pink Granite Coast (Ploumanac'h, Perros-Guirec) is possible at an additional charge. The return Paris to Saint-Brieuc is available at the same rate.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TGV Saint-Brieuc — Paris costs 30-90 euros and takes about 2h45 direct, but direct services are limited — many trains require a connection at Rennes (minimum 15 min wait). FlixBus connects Saint-Brieuc to Paris in 6h for 20-40 euros. The TaxiNeo taxi at 490 — 590 euros is the ultimate door-to-door comfort solution. For 4 passengers (123-148 euros per person), the cost is comparable to first-class TGV, with the advantage of a direct journey with no connections and all luggage included.",
