        comparaisonTransport: "There is no direct TER train between Dinan and Rennes — you must go via Dol-de-Bretagne or Saint-Brieuc, making the journey 1h30-2h with a connection. The BreizhGo bus (line 10) links Dinan to Rennes in about 1h15 for 6 euros, with 4-5 departures daily on weekdays. BlaBlaCar offers rides from 4 euros. The TaxiNeo taxi at 60 — 75 euros is the only direct door-to-door option with no connections, in just 40 minutes. For 3-4 passengers (15-25 euros per person), it is extremely competitive against public transport, especially in time saved.",
